post.description:
All query params are optional, now nested dynamic object can also be searched

supported logical operators:

```
"$lt"      ( number_field: {"$lt": number} )
"$lte"     ( number_field: {"$lte": number} )
"$gt"      ( number_field: {"$gt": number} )
"$gte"     ( number_field: {"$gte": number} )

"$inclusiveBetween" (number_field: {"$inclusiveBetween": [3, 6]})
"$exclusiveBetween" (number_field: {"$exclusiveBetween": [1, 8]})

"$contains"      (array_of_something_field: {"$contains": obj_or_value})
"$notContains"

"$is"        (anything_field: {"$is": anything})
"$isNot"

"$isOneOf"   (value_or_object_field: {"$isOneOf": [something, something]})
"$isNotOneOf"

"$stringContains" (string_field: {"$stringContains": "<substring>"})
"$stringNotContains"
```

```javascript
{
  "blockchain_network": "TESTNET_LEAFCHAIN_SAND",
  "metadata": {
    "static": {
      "attributes": {
        "$elementMatch": {
          "trait_type": "timezone"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

L1 mints nft collection in batch [v2],  
if this is the first time minting nfts in `collection_custom_id`,  
the nft with `serial_number=0` will be the representative nft of this collection
